Getting Started / Setup (Example)

> **Note:** Adjust for your preferred stack (e.g. backend, memory store, tool modules).  

```bash
# Clone the repo
git clone https://github.com/phoenicon/aigent.farm.git
cd aigent.farm

# (Optional) create virtual environment
python -m venv venv
source venv/bin/activate

# Install dependencies (if any)
# e.g. pip install -r requirements.txt

# Configure memory backend / API keys / data sources  
# Modify config file or environment variables as required

# Run agent in demo / interactive mode  
python run_agent.py  # or equivalent entrypoint

# (Optional) run tests / example scripts  
python examples/demo_env.py  

 Who Is This For?

Developers building AI agents that need long-term memory, real-world context, and asset integration

Builders in AgriTech, ESG data, real-world asset tokenization, Web3, DeFi, RWA

Anyone exploring modular, transparent, auditable agent systems rather than opaque black-box LLM wrappers
